The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, July 21: Magna International is planning to set up a manufacturing facility in India to manufacture multiple vehicles from a single facility. The company is exploring possibilities to set up the plant to cater to the needs and requirements of different auto makers, a company spokesperson said.                             
	 Mumbai, July 21: Sebi has done away with the practice of keeping shares under no-delivery during the record date for corporate announcements such as bonus or dividend to avoid volatility in the markets. No-delivery period means that trading during the record date would not result in any delivery of shares.                            
	 New Delhi, July 21: The price band for Adani Powers initial public offering, which will hit the market on July 28, has been fixed at Rs 90-100 per share. Adani Power has already filed the draft red herring prospectus with market regulator Sebi.                            
	 New Delhi, July 21: Indias wheat production touched an all-time high of 80.58 million tonnes in the 2008-09 crop year, while rice output rose to a record 99.15 million tonnes on high support prices to farmers.                             
	 Calcutta, July 21: Bajaj Auto, which re-entered the volume driven 100cc bike segment recently, is eyeing the market leader position in eastern India by the end of the festive season, sales manager (east) K.B. Mohanty said.                                                                                                                           
